 ('148', '124', '16', '1', 'en_ie', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"16\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Sonica Fitout\",\"slug\":\"sonica-fitout\",\"postDate\":1518716640,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"57\":\"<p>We are delighted to showcase the completion of our new Head Office in Kingram Place, at the heart of Fitzwilliam Square in Dublin City Center.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Works commenced in January 2016 and were completed in a hugely impressive 5-week programme led by our D&B CM Colin Kirwan. Calling on our most trusted of trade contract partners, we have succeeded in creating what we feel is an office that\\u2019s truly worthy of the people that occupy it. It is everything we are as a Company: unique, unconventional, unexpected, refreshingly modern and forward thinking.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The fitout is nothing short of breath taking. Justin Treacy and Liat Greenhot of RKD Interiors have taken the vibrancy and energy of the Sonica brand and brought it to life with a myriad of individual features and wonderful ideas. From the floor-to-ceiling trapezoidal wall panelled boardroom to a 10m long 3-D snake bench with over 300 individually milled vertical components in the Ops Area, there is simply nothing like it in the City.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>We can\\u2019t wait to show you around what is a great place to work and even better place to visit!<\\/p>\",\"60\":\"<ul><li>Unique custom made trapezoidal Boardroom wall panelling<\\/li><li>Completely bespoke joinery throughout the entire office<\\/li><li>Feature operator workstation desking & storage units<\\/li><li>Wifi controlled lighting control system for user defined mood and colour settings<\\/li><li>Extensive graphics and artwork package<\\/li><li>Custom laid vinyl plank flooring to feature guest Reception<\\/li><li>Complete A\\/V solution to Boardroom, Breakouts and Reception.<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"63\":\"\",\"56\":\"Kingram Place, Dublin 2\",\"64\":\"\",\"61\":\"This office is our showroom, our statement of \\\"Hey, look what we can do!\\\" and it does that all in spades. We love seeing peoples reactions when they visit because they are just simply blown away with the ideas and concepts, the intricacies of the work and the overall finished product. In almost 20-years of fitout, I\'m happy to say there is simply nothing like it anywhere else, which is what we at Sonica are all about.\",\"62\":\"Donnacha Neary, Managing Director\",\"58\":\"<ul><li>350m2<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"59\":\"<ul><li>5 weeks on site<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}}', '2018-02-15 18:14:19', '2018-02-15 18:14:19', '526a9245-80ed-433d-ac16-f98a71a8e51b'),
 ('149', '125', '16', '1', 'en_ie', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"16\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Ellucian\",\"slug\":\"ellucian\",\"postDate\":1518716640,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"57\":\"<p>Ellucian provide the software, services and analytics needed to manage campus businesses faster, easier and more effectively. Serving 2,400 institutions in 40 countries across the globe, they selected Sonica Fitout as their partner for the fitout of their new Irish HQ in Dublin.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The project commenced with the demolition and strip out of existing finishes and M&E services on one of the upper floors of this multi-tenanted, fully occupied live building. The pre-planning and logistical management of this significant operation ran hand-in-hand with the simultaneous upfront procurement of specialist packages required for the fitout.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The intricate design of the space encompassed features on all flat surfaces, from the multi-layered flooring finishes to the varied hard and soft textures on partitions and walls throughout. The open plan desking has privacy screens and operator chairs matched with selected fabrics to accentuate the colour scheme of the Company\\u2019s brand. Ceilings were a blend of exposed concrete slabs interspersed with raft formed lay in grids to pick out areas below. A full M&E, IT and A\\/V brief fell under our remit with Sonica also co-ordinating the Client furniture delivery, load-out and installation.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The completed space gives staff the use of finished huddle rooms, spacious canteens and tea stations, open collaboration areas, V-Con Rooms, Exec Boardrooms and quiet cellular offices. The project was delivered on-programme and within the agreed Contract Sum. More importantly, it was a hugely enjoyable experience for us thanks to a fantastic Client that empowered their Design Team to \\u201cgo big\\u201d with their imagination and trusted us to realise their vision for the completed work space.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The end product is truly spectacular, one that we are hugely proud of and delighted to show case.<\\/p>\",\"60\":\"<ul><li>Substantial feature joinery package<\\/li><li>Acoustically rated glazed partition solution with bespoke manifestations<\\/li><li>Complete M&E refit with Data \\/ Active IT rewire part of brief<\\/li><li>Multiple floor finishes, hard and soft<\\/li><li>Co-ordination with sitting tennants and Landlord teams all through construction<\\/li><li>Snag free hand back<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"63\":\"\",\"56\":\"Marine House, Dublin 2\",\"64\":\"\",\"61\":\"A very detailed piece of work taken on and delivered against an aggressive programme driven by our Client\'s not to be missed occupational requirements. You guys made it all look easy.\",\"62\":\"Neil McGovern, Project Manager & Client Rep. Jones Lang LaSalle\",\"58\":\"<ul><li>1000m2 floor plate<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"59\":\"<ul><li>7 weeks on-site from start to full Client occupation<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}}', '2018-02-15 18:14:30', '2018-02-15 18:14:30', '69707c78-9d3b-448c-85ad-b202c21b6039'),
 ('150', '126', '16', '1', 'en_ie', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"16\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Ticket Master\",\"slug\":\"ticket-master\",\"postDate\":1518716640,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"57\":\"<p>Ticketmaster is the world\\u2019s largest ticket distribution company,&nbsp;providing event&nbsp;tickets for more than 10,000 Promotors whose productions range from professional wrestling matches and rock concerts to Broadway shows and operas.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Our brief was to deliver a vibrant and invigorating work space for the Company\\u2019s employees at the new Ticketmaster Ireland HQ. &nbsp;The works entailed the fit-out to an existing unit which involved strip out and demolitions of the previously occupied space, the installation of all new wall partitions, floor finishes, internal decoration, M&E service&nbsp;installations and a complete office furniture solution. &nbsp;The design of the working environment is predominantly open plan to allow for collaborative interaction and employee connectivity, but strategically placed workstations and cellular meeting spaces ensure that teams retain their structure within the overall environment.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Features of the design include a spacious staff kitchen and breakout area, a specialised digital meeting \\/ training room, boardroom, numerous meeting rooms, a secure ticket print \\/ store room and a reception area with \\u201cBolon\\u201d wall and bespoke desk. &nbsp;In keeping with Ticketmasters corporate brand identity, large scale graphics fill the walls at every vantage point, reinforcing the culture of the company and adding energy and colour to the space.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The project was delivered in&nbsp;6 weeks following an accelerated pre-construction and mobilisation period to meet the Clients set in stone move in date.<\\/p>\",\"60\":\"<ul><li>Bespoke specialised joinery with numerous unique finishes and materials<\\/li><li>International collaboration with Ticket Master\\u2019s overseas steering group<\\/li><li>Corporate signage & brand identity<\\/li><li>Management of Client direct vend packages<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"63\":\"\",\"56\":\"Grafton House, Grafton Street\",\"64\":\"\",\"61\":\"\",\"62\":\"\",\"58\":\"<ul><li>600m2<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"59\":\"<ul><li>2 weeks pre-con<\\/li><li>6 weeks on site<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}}', '2018-02-15 18:14:39', '2018-02-15 18:14:39', '2c216e91-5da2-4035-a12d-447a37825c1f'),
 ('151', '127', '16', '1', 'en_ie', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"16\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Wipro\",\"slug\":\"wipro-2\",\"postDate\":1518716640,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"57\":\"<p>Wipro Ltd is a global information technology, consulting and outsourcing company with 158,217 employees serving clients in 175+ cities across 6 continents. The company posted revenues of $7.5 billion for the financial year ended Mar 31, 2015.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Following their announcement to move into the Irish market, they selected Sonica as their turn key D&B contractor for the design and fitout of their new 240-seater office in the spectacular Elm Park OBA in Dublin.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Our Design and Build brief took the project from initial space planning for Lease negotiation, to Landlord consent phase, through to detailed design, costing, planning, constructing and overall hand-back. The complete project life cycle, managed from start-to-finish by Sonica.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Works were undertaken in the top 3-floors of the OBA building with management of logistics and daily co-ordination with the sitting Building Management Team a key consideration in the development of our aggressive construction programme.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>A high degree of cellularisation in forming the various manager offices, meeting spaces, huddle rooms and executive boardrooms required considerable addition to the Landlords naturally conditioned eco-building ventilation strategy via. intensive modelling and BMS integration. The project scope also included a large specialist joinery component, stone flooring, substantial active IT solution, a fully redundant IT backbone install, Comms Room UPS, digital monitoring, building security, A\\/V delivery and a complete furniture installation across 3-floor plates.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The project was run with fully transparent financials, with the Client retaining all expenditure authorisation throughout the build process via their internationally issued PO\\u2019s. The completed works were delivered below the original approved budget tabled at Design completion stage.<\\/p>\",\"60\":\"<ul><li>International collaboration at design phase to achieve Client design goals.<\\/li><li>Open plan financials with project delivered on time and below budget.<\\/li><li>Comms room commissioned and complete 3 weeks before handover to allow Client IT access.<\\/li><li>Client direct vendors were managed into our overall programme to ensure complete co-ordination of overall project completion.<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"63\":\"\",\"56\":\"Elm Park, Dublin\",\"64\":\"\",\"61\":\"Every member of their Project Delivery Team remained a hugely visible resource to us all through the complete project life cycle and the final results speak for themselves. We cannot speak highly enough of the manner in which they completed this project.\",\"62\":\"Paul Quinn, BKD Architects.\",\"58\":\"<ul><li>3,000m2<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"59\":\"<ul><li>6 weeks design<\\/li><li>8 weeks on site<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}}', '2018-02-15 18:14:52', '2018-02-15 18:14:52', '718065ad-dac5-49ea-9ddb-de2a355fb8b4'),
 ('152', '128', '16', '1', 'en_ie', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"16\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Blackrock Investments\",\"slug\":\"blackrock-investments\",\"postDate\":1518716640,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"57\":\"<p>Blackrock is trusted to manage more money than any other investment firm with over 135 teams in 30 countries sharing their best thinking to seek better returns for their clients. As the worlds largest investor, they currently manage in excess of 7,700 portfolios comprising $4.72T of assets.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Following the expansion of their Irish Team, they selected Sonica as main contractor for their office relocation project as they transferred their Dublin operation from Barrow St. to larger offices in Ballsbridge.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Our brief took the project from an empty \\u201cgrey box\\u201d to their fully fitted out Corporate HQ in 14 weeks from appointment.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Works were undertaken in a multi-tenanted fully occupied building with continual intensive daily co-ordination with the sitting Building Management Team and other tenants a key consideration in the development of our aggressive construction programme.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Due to the high degree of cellularisation to form the various manager offices, meeting spaces and executive boardrooms, the mechanical scope required considerable addition to the primary Landlord ventilation provisions via. intensive upgrades, modelling and BMS integration. The project scope also included a large specialist joinery component, a bespoke reception area, feature hard and soft floorings, substantial active IT solution, a fully redundant IT backbone install, Comms Room UPS & downflow A\\/C, programmable SCADA digital monitoring, high-end Corporate level access control and security install, A\\/V delivery and a full furniture installation across the complete floor plate.<br>All works were completed on-time against an aggressive delivery programme and within the agreed budget parameters.<\\/p>\",\"60\":\"<ul><li>International collaboration with UK led Design Team<\\/li><li>Co-ordination with sitting tenants and Landlord Teams throughout the construction period<\\/li><li>Comms room commissioned and complete 2 weeks before handover to allow Client IT access.<\\/li><li>Client direct vendors were managed into our overall programme to ensure complete co-ordination of the overall project completion<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"63\":\"\",\"56\":\"Ballsbridge\",\"64\":\"\",\"61\":\"\",\"62\":\"\",\"58\":\"<ul><li>1,000m2<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"59\":\"<ul><li>4 weeks Pre-Con<\\/li><li>10 weeks on site<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}}', '2018-02-15 18:15:01', '2018-02-15 18:15:01', '92d62208-5c2d-4d0f-97ce-4fcb63614b82'),
 ('153', '129', '16', '1', 'en_ie', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"16\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Nissan\",\"slug\":\"nissan\",\"postDate\":1518716640,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"57\":\"<p>Nissan has been at the forefront of the Irish motor industry since their arrival into Ireland in 1977, a feat that is achieved by a potent combination of aggressive sales and marketing strategies coupled with an extremely strong customer service philosophy.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>As part of their continual commitment to maintaining top-end customer experiences in their network of dealer garages, the Company embarked on a programme of refurbishment on four of their flag-ship premises in Deansgrange, Liffey Valley, Airside Swords and Tallaght. We were delighted to be selected by Nissan and their extended Professional Team to carry out this exciting multi-location works programme.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The works centred on the strip out and replacement of key features and finishes in the existing garages to raise their already impressive profiles. This was achieved by the introduction of a new bespoke A\\/V installation, a feature lighting overhaul, addition of glazed meeting rooms for customer interaction, a total hard-flooring uplift and replacement, new joinery, soft furnishings and a full redecoration to create a completely new look-and-feel.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The biggest challenge was to carry out these works, against 4-separate and standalone aggressive installation programmes, whilst the garages remained open for business during the refurbishment process.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>It is a testament to the on-site management from the Sonica Operations Team that the projects were not only all completed on-time, but the positive impact achieved through the high-quality of the finished works exceeded Nissan\\u2019s initial expectations for these flag-ship finished garages.<\\/p>\",\"60\":\"<ul><li>Full strip out of existing finishes carried out inside LIVE working garages<\\/li><li>Substantial out of hours working to facilitate Sales Operations<\\/li><li>Co-ordination of Client direct international suppliers<\\/li><li>Phased programming to allow staggered completion of garages<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"63\":\"\",\"56\":\"Dublin\",\"64\":\"\",\"61\":\"We developed a very good relationship with Sonica during the course of our recent multi-location refurbishments. We felt that the lines of communication were always open, their Team were very responsive to our various queries whilst remaining extremely flexible, but most importantly they shared our passion and commitment for the project at hand. We are simply delighted with the final product.\",\"62\":\"Ian Moran, Group Financial Accountant\",\"58\":\"<ul><li>4 no. garages of 1500m2 each<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"59\":\"<ul><li>4 weeks per garage<\\/li><li>16-week overall programme<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}}', '2018-02-15 18:15:09', '2018-02-15 18:15:09', 'cce0ab1d-fc46-4d85-b03f-f0d9d3134be0'),
 ('154', '130', '16', '1', 'en_ie', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"16\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Private Client\",\"slug\":\"private-client-5\",\"postDate\":1518716640,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"57\":\"<p>Our Client is one of Ireland\\u2019s leading providers of advanced information technology, products, services and business consulting expertise. They are dedicated to helping their Clients innovate and succeed through the end-to-end transformation of their business models and the application of innovative technology and business solutions.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Our brief comprised of the creation of a new customer experience room at their main operations facility in Dublin. Works were undertaken within this heavily occupied building with continual intensive daily co-ordination with the on-site Building Management Team. The existing space was previously used as a games area, the new fit-out required strip out of all existing finishes to provide a significant AV installation to the room, together with extensive modifications to the \\u201cStreet\\u201d circulation and access areas. An associated AV room and Store Room was also constructed.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The finished product is a sleek modern fitout and the use of corporate colours throughout the design is a bold injection into what was previosuly a neutral space. Some highly technical features on the project included a bespoke free standing feature wall that was constructed with a steel frame and wrapped in toughened back painted glass to act as a divider in the room to separate the space. A custom built curved glass ramp was also provided and hanging feature oval lights are an uplifting addition.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The project was completed within the agreed tender time frame of 5 weeks.<\\/p>\",\"60\":\"<ul><li>Bespoke free standing feature wall<\\/li><li>Specialist feature lighting<\\/li><li>Hi-Tech AV interactive and communications systems<\\/li><li>Curved glass access ramp<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"63\":\"\",\"56\":\"Dublin\",\"64\":\"\",\"61\":\"\",\"62\":\"\",\"58\":\"<ul><li>150m2<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"59\":\"<ul><li>5 weeks on site<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}}', '2018-02-15 18:15:15', '2018-02-15 18:15:15', '4164d02b-7504-41ab-958b-5cb54725a701'),
 ('155', '131', '16', '1', 'en_ie', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"16\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Guinness Storehouse\",\"slug\":\"guinness-storehouse\",\"postDate\":1518716640,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"57\":\"<p>Spread over 4-floors, works ran concurrently in Ireland\\u2019s No. 1 Tourist attraction \\u2013 a building with 5,000 visitors daily.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Individual work areas were the Visitor Experience Center, Group Orientation area, Arthur Guinness Room, Business Center refurbishment, Project Taste Experience, Arrol Bar refurbishment, Red Jacket retail Fitout, Ground Floor signature St. James\\u2019s Gate Replica and a full mezzanine retail area re-fit.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Project Taste included conceptual \\u201cScent Oscillator\\u201d columns, developed and designed specifically for the new Taste Experience exhibition. The main ingredients used to brew Guinness were vaporized to enhance the overall visitor sensory experience in tasting the beer.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Interactive A\\/V screens in The Arthur Guinness Room that speak to visitors as they pass. Screen chassis\\u2019s concealed within feature wall paneling and triggered from ceiling disguised presence detectors.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>A full size replica of the iconic St. James\\u2019s Gate was installed in the main Ground Floor visitor reception area.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Restoration of historic Guinness photography for scanning and printing onto full size extended wall murals installed in the Group Reception Area.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Millwork fabricated from reclaimed sources to preserve the antique feel of several feature joinery pieces.<\\/p>\",\"60\":\"<ul><li>Multi-Trade Interaction and Co-ordination<\\/li><li>Management of incumbent contractors within main fitout programme<\\/li><li>Extensive OOH Works to accommodate visitor traffic<\\/li><li>Concept Design Development<\\/li><li>Interaction with Several Design Teams across concurrent projects<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"63\":\"\",\"56\":\"St James\\u2019s Gate, Dublin 8\",\"64\":\"\",\"61\":\"We wanted this scheme to become the best place to taste Guiness Worldwide. The outcome conceived and developed by your installation team is simply outstanding. It has exceeded all my expectations. I love Taste, but more importantly, our visitors love it.\",\"62\":\"Paul Carthy, Managing Director, Guinness Storehouse\",\"58\":\"<ul><li>Multiple individual work areas spread over 4-separate floors.<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"59\":\"<ul><li>22 weeks on site<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}}', '2018-02-15 18:15:29', '2018-02-15 18:15:29', 'fbe3f94b-082a-48f1-b655-2c2cabb8dfcd'),
 ('156', '132', '16', '1', 'en_ie', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"16\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Fitter Faster Stronger\",\"slug\":\"fitter-faster-stronger-1\",\"postDate\":1518716640,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"57\":\"<p>Having only formed in 2013, Fitter Faster Stronger (FFS) is now widely regarded as the pre-eminent Strength, Metabolic Conditioning and Functional Training Facility in the Capital.&nbsp; Founded by Rory McInerney and Ciaran Ruddock, they have already cultivated a unique brand, a large Twitter following and a dedicated membership that has christened their training facility \\u201cThe Home of Hard Work\\u201c.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>As part of their expansion and continual brand development, we were hugely enthusiastic to be engaged for their gym refurbishment project on Leeson St.&nbsp; With three of the Senior Sonica management staff already dedicated members of the gym, we were delighted to be able to offer some of our expertise back in return for the countless hours of training and coaching we had received from the FFS Team.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The brief was to draw heavily from the already established branding and colouring of the FFS logo, and transfer that strength of identity into the various training areas of the gym.&nbsp; The results are clean, sharp surfaces throughout with extensive motivational branding & calls to action.<\\/p>\",\"60\":\"<ul><li>Concept development<\\/li><li>Design and off-site fabrication<\\/li><li>Extensive branding and signage<\\/li><li>Bespoke branded cabinetry and joinery<\\/li><li>Feature Gym Flooring<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"63\":\"\",\"56\":\"Leeson Street\",\"64\":\"\",\"61\":\"The level of professionalism and proficiency astounded us on this project. The entire revamp was completed on an aggressive timeline, a 36 hour period, in order to minimise downtime for our Clients. The team at FFS are all delighted with a gym that is now more functional, but also looks awesome!\",\"62\":\"Rory McInerney, Managing Director, FFS\",\"58\":\"<ul><li>Basement area, City Centre Location.<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"59\":\"<ul><li>The project was fully designed and off-site fabricated, assembly occurred on-site over a single out-of-hours weekend to accommodate the extensive gym class schedule.<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}}', '2018-02-15 18:15:39', '2018-02-15 18:15:39', '19513a48-f4e1-4b25-a60c-0498d933f910'),
 ('157', '133', '16', '1', 'en_ie', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"16\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Ballsbridge Park\",\"slug\":\"ballsbridge-park\",\"postDate\":1518716640,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"57\":\"<p>Landlord refurbishment project to recondition the building atrium and main reception, all lift cores, common areas, bathrooms and staircores spread over 6-floors in a Live occupied working environment.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Works also extended to the complete demolition and refitting of the Ground Floor Open Plan Offices to act as the building marketing suite.<br>Formation of ground floor meeting rooms for anchor tenant, specifically designed for maximum privacy with increased acoustic properties.<br>Reflooring complete atrium with new stone tiling \\u2013 all works carried out by nights to minimize disruption to existing tenants.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Installation of new enlarged multi-operator reception desk, double height feature atrium wall paneling and glazing.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Building fabric surveying and development of repair and maintenance programme.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Installation of new security speed lanes with supply of access control systems tailored to multitenant \\/ multi-card operation.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Complete M&E brief to include all services associated with bathroom and shower upgrades, A\\/C to open plan offices and power upgrades to suit new tenancy requirements.<\\/p>\",\"60\":\"<ul><li>Landlord \\/ Tennant liaison in programme development<\\/li><li>Large proportion of works undertaken out of hours<\\/li><li>Feature package design development with architect to align with budget provisions<\\/li><li>Interfacing with multiple stake holders<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"63\":\"\",\"56\":\"Sweepstakes Building, Dublin 4\",\"64\":\"\",\"61\":\"We were very impressed by the manner in which you undertook the project and advanced your works \\u2013 nothing was ever an issue, \\u201cNo\\u201d was never an answer.\",\"62\":\"Frank Doyle, Studio 3 Architects\",\"58\":\"<ul><li>Multiple individual work areas spread over 6-separate floors.<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"59\":\"<ul><li>14 weeks on site<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}}', '2018-02-15 18:15:51', '2018-02-15 18:15:51', '7f4b84bb-26f5-44c2-8ff9-9dd43a450eca'),
 ('158', '133', '16', '1', 'en_ie', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"16\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Ballsbridge Park\",\"slug\":\"ballsbridge-park\",\"postDate\":1518716640,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"57\":\"<p>Landlord refurbishment project to recondition the building atrium and main reception, all lift cores, common areas, bathrooms and staircores spread over 6-floors in a Live occupied working environment.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Works also extended to the complete demolition and refitting of the Ground Floor Open Plan Offices to act as the building marketing suite.<br>Formation of ground floor meeting rooms for anchor tenant, specifically designed for maximum privacy with increased acoustic properties.<br>Reflooring complete atrium with new stone tiling \\u2013 all works carried out by nights to minimize disruption to existing tenants.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Installation of new enlarged multi-operator reception desk, double height feature atrium wall paneling and glazing.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Building fabric surveying and development of repair and maintenance programme.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Installation of new security speed lanes with supply of access control systems tailored to multitenant \\/ multi-card operation.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Complete M&E brief to include all services associated with bathroom and shower upgrades, A\\/C to open plan offices and power upgrades to suit new tenancy requirements.<\\/p>\",\"60\":\"<ul><li>Landlord \\/ Tennant liaison in programme development<\\/li><li>Large proportion of works undertaken out of hours<\\/li><li>Feature package design development with architect to align with budget provisions<\\/li><li>Interfacing with multiple stake holders<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"63\":\"\",\"56\":\"Sweepstakes Building, Dublin 4\",\"64\":\"\",\"61\":\"We were very impressed by the manner in which you undertook the project and advanced your works \\u2013 nothing was ever an issue, \\u201cNo\\u201d was never an answer.\",\"62\":\"Frank Doyle, Studio 3 Architects\",\"58\":\"<ul><li>Multiple individual work areas spread over 6-separate floors.<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"59\":\"<ul><li>14 weeks on site<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}}', '2018-02-15 18:16:00', '2018-02-15 18:16:00', '58ab4491-e489-4d18-be74-9c2b8e7915cc'),
 ('159', '134', '16', '1', 'en_ie', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"16\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Aspen Pharma\",\"slug\":\"aspen-pharma\",\"postDate\":1518716640,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"57\":\"<p>Design and Build project from initial space planning for Lease negotiation, to Landlord consent phase, through to detailed design, costing, planning, constructing and overall hand-back. The complete project life cycle, managed from start-to-finish by Sonica.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Open plan spaces were developed off the Client\\u2019s international office templates, with the expressed requirement to improve existing flow and promote productivity. Our designers took the starting point from a Dubai based plan and streamlined it into an improved Dublin model to achieve these goals.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Works were undertaken inside a 12-storey multi tenanted building. Management of logistics and daily co-ordination with the sitting Building Management Team was a key consideration in the development of our aggressive construction programme which was led by Client early occupational requirements.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>A high degree of cellularisation in the offices required considerable addition to the Landlord provided A\\/C and lighting control systems. These A\\/C & lighting upgrades were carried out to provide local dedicated user defined control and were simultaneously linked back to the head end BMS system for Landlord energy monitoring.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The project was run as an open book Management Contract, with the Client retaining all expenditure authorization throughout the build process. The completed works were delivered below the original approved budget tabled at Design completion stage.<\\/p>\",\"60\":\"<ul><li>International collaboration at design phase to achieve Client design goals.<\\/li><li>Open plan financials with project delivered on time and below budget.<\\/li><li>Comms room commissioned and complete 3 weeks before handover to allow Client IT access.<\\/li><li>Client direct vendors were managed into our overall programme to ensure complete co-ordination of overall project completion.<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"63\":\"\",\"56\":\"Custom House Quay, Dublin 2\",\"64\":\"\",\"61\":\"From initial meeting to final handback, we knew that in Sonica Fitout we had a Design & Build Contractor that could translate the multi-faceted requirements of our business needs into a single, co-ordinated and stream lined project action plan. They listened, they advised and they delivered a space that has gone way beyoned all of our expectations.\",\"62\":\"Elisha O\' Keeffe, Aspen Pharma Ireland\",\"58\":\"<ul><li>750m2<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"59\":\"<ul><li>8 weeks on site<\\/li><\\/ul>\"}}', '2018-02-15 18:16:12', '2018-02-15 18:16:12', 'c5a7cec3-3ef7-40b0-b0f4-8c0d9d4ad6c4'),
 ('160', '135', '16', '1', 'en_ie', '2', '', '{\"typeId\":\"16\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Sonica HQ\",\"slug\":\"sonica-hq\",\"postDate\":1518716640,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"57\":\"<p>The brief was to capture the vibrancy and energy of the Sonica Fitout brand, while showcasing our talent for design and fitout.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The completed office had to deliver a working area that would encourage open collaboration between departments and provide an environment where staff could discuss fresh ideas and develop new systems.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The Company branding and instantly recognisable \\u201cSonica Rainbow\\u201d colouring were used as the central theme in the fitout, with graphics and murals developed specifically to enhance the fabrics, wall and floor colorings used throughout.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Staff & Client individuality was celebrated with offices and meeting rooms designed with personality.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The canteen has a \\u201cCatch Phrase Wall\\u201d dedicated to valued Company friend.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The sauna styled Collab Room succeeds in forming the central hub \\u2013 a place we gravitate to for both informal internal meetings and TGI Friday beers.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>The Strong Room is a \\u201cDo Not Disturb Zone\\u201d where we can go to crash out a tender or just think in peace and quiet.<\\/p>\\r\\n<p>Our Client\\u2019s love it too \\u2013 we\\u2019ve lost track of the amount of people that have called in to us, just to hang out (and to make sure they get their names onto the Sonica Tube Map!)<\\/p>\",\"60\":\"<ul><li>Sauna style Collab area<\\/li><li>Extensive bespoke murals and wall art<\\/li><li>Feature wall tiling and lighting throughout<\\/li><li>Executive Boardroom with full A\\/V<\\/li><li>Strong Room \\/ Phone Free Zone for thinking.<\\/li><\\/ul>\",\"63\":\"\",\"56\":\"10-12 Hogan Place, Dublin 2\",\"64\":\"\",\"61\":\"It\\u2019s a really nice space, an office we all feel comfortable in, a place we love to work in, our home away from home.\",\"62\":\"Donnacha Neary, MD, Sonica Fitout\",\"58\":\"<p>300m2<\\/p>\",\"59\":\"<p>3 weeks on site.<\\/p>\"}}', '2018-02-15 18:16:17', '2018-02-15 18:16:17', '4e26dead-6708-42ff-b44b-b969f498d02c'),
